Similar Songs


This page has three sections: user submissions, songs I think sound similar, and a snapshot from SoundsJustLike.com.

I hope these lists help people discover new music and find those songs that are on the tip of their ears. They've already helped me rediscover a similar-sounding song I couldn't figure out from memory alone.

To search, use your browser's built-in find-on-page functionality: Command+F, Ctrl+F, or on iOS tap into the address bar and type the text to find on page.

If you can't find what you're looking for, check out WhoSampled.com or try humming/singing into SoundHound.

Learn more about this page here.

You can

submit similar songs you'd like to see on this page

I originally started this list in a post. To make this page more complete, I stopped updating that post and list these here instead.

Here are some of my favorite direct samples, confirmed on WhoSampled.com:

- Seth Everman combining Moonlight Sonata and Still D.R.E.

These songs remind me of each other. Maybe the songs share a similar palette, a similar bassline, or similar instruments:

- Shared characteristic: eerie robotic beeps and boops
  - Pure Imagination by Fiona Apple
    - See also Chipotle's Scarecrow video that features the same song
    - Note that this song is a cover of Gene Wilder's original rendition in Willy Wonka & the Chocolate Factory
  - Terry Time from Pixar's Soul by Trent Reznor and Atticus Ross
  - Dr. Ford from Westworld Season 1 Soundtrack by Ramin Djawadi

- Shared characteristic: late 90s alt rock
  - Sunday Morning by No Doubt
  - Having An Average Weekend (aka the theme song to Kids in the Hall) by Shadowy Men on a Shadowy Planet

- Similar chord progression
  - Dear Prudence by The Beatles
  - Beautiful by Christina Aguilera

- Similar cadence, lyrics, and Paul McCartney sound
  - Dear Prudence by The Beatles
  - Wonderful Christmastime by Paul McCartney

- Similar vocalization of "oooOOoohhh"
  - Oh by Ciara
  - Do It to It by Cherish, later remade by Acraze ft. Cherish. And there's a really cool mash-up with an eerie song from Squid Game by Zedd.

- Similar to Show Me by Dexys Midnight Runners
